1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,100
<i> Call that Anne Gomez</i>

2
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:13,833
<i>and tell her
I will double the pay</i>

3
00:00:13,967 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>as long as she can arrange
the wedding in one month.</i>

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,933
<i>I want you to stop
showing up to us.</i>

5
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,167
<i> That's what I want.</i>

6
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:21,100
<i>Your daughter doesn't
respect you anymore.</i>

7
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,100
<i>And you're still
going to chase her?</i>

8
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> It's none of your business.</i>

9
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:24,233
<i> It is.</i>

10
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:25,300
<i> Because I love you.</i>

11
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:28,900
<i>From now on,
we will build a happy world</i>

12
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:32,167
<i>where Emma doesn't exist,
it will be just the three of us.</i>

13
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,967
<i>Why did you pack your bags
and leave your boss?</i>

14
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,667
<i> Please come home.</i>

15
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,267
<i>I don't want to see you
in the meantime.</i>

16
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,100
<i> Or talk about your feelings.</i>

17
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:44,967
<i> Congratulations!</i>

18
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,800
<i>Even Mookie has already
pushed you away.</i>

19
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>I won't stop trying to win
her over</i>

20
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:52,133
<i>until she gets tired
of pushing me away.</i>

21
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:53,200
<i> Until she listens to me.</i>

22
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,667
<i> Until she believes me.</i>

23
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,433
<i> I will never stop.</i>

24
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:35,767
Are you okay?

25
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,767
- Here's your drink.
- Yeah, I'm fine.

26
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:38,833
Thank you.

27
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:41,733
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

28
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:43,333
I'll join Noel for a bit, okay?

29
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:44,167
Okay.

30
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,933
Of course, I'm bothered that
Emma's stalking Mookie.

31
00:02:09,067 --> 00:02:12,133
Especially since I don't know
what's on Logan's mind.

32
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:14,767
And what he's capable of doing.

33
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:17,100
But you know what?

34
00:02:17,233 --> 00:02:22,233
I think I already know
what Emma's weakness is.

35
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:27,733
It's seeing Danilo, Mookie,
and I together.

36
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:33,867
She loses her focus
whenever she sees us together.

37
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,133
<i> Do you have a plan?</i>

38
00:02:38,967 --> 00:02:40,333
You bet I do.

39
00:02:56,367 --> 00:02:57,633
Emma.

40
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,333
Emma, are you okay?

41
00:02:59,467 --> 00:03:00,733
What do you need?

42
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:01,867
Wine?

43
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,767
Beer? Have some liquor to
somehow ease your anger.

44
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:07,133
No, I'm okay.

45
00:03:07,267 --> 00:03:09,733
Thank you, Flor.

46
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:12,533
Are you sure?

47
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:16,167
Hey, thank you
for giving me a job.

48
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:20,200
I'll leave you for now.

49
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,133
I'll go back to what I'm doing.

50
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,800
- Okay.
- Will you be okay?

51
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:25,033
Yes.

52
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:36,600
Mommy?

53
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:40,233
Yes, baby girl.

54
00:03:40,367 --> 00:03:41,100
Are you okay?

55
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:43,233
- Of course!
- Are you having fun?

56
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:45,467
The best time!

57
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,267
Are you happy with the
party I arranged for you?

58
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:51,000
I super appreciate it,
baby girl.

59
00:03:51,133 --> 00:03:53,600
You're the best.

60
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,800
I love you, Mommy.

61
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:58,500
Mommy, I'll just
use the restroom.

62
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:01,133
Can you please hold my bag?

63
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:02,167
Sure.

64
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:02,933
Thank you.

65
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:04,733
You're the best!

66
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:37,900
Mookie sent me a message.

67
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:45,033
She has unblocked me.

68
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:48,167
<i> Mommy Jade talked to me, Mom.</i>

69
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:51,333
<i>Let's talk and settle things
once and for all.</i>

70
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:54,067
<i>Let's meet tomorrow
at lunch time.</i>

71
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:57,367
<i>At the Sapphire Banquet Hall
of Liberty Pacific Hotel.</i>

72
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,100
<i> Yes, Dear. I'll be there.</i>

73
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:22,700
Mommy Jade, Dad...

74
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,400
The food tasting won't
take long, right?

75
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,733
I have to go somewhere.

76
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:31,767
Wait, where are you going?

77
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,067
Are you going on a date?

78
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,133
Chill, Love!

79
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,067
A date already?

80
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:39,100
She's going to watch a movie
with Cacai and Zayn.

81
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:40,667
So, it's not a date.

82
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,533
Make sure it's not a date.

83
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:44,500
Yes.

84
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:46,067
Zayn must ask
for my permission first

85
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,300
if he wants to date you.

86
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:52,633
If not, I'll spank both of you.

87
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:55,933
Come on, Love.

88
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:57,333
Really, spank?

89
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:59,233
What do you think of them?

90
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:00,833
Kids?

91
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:03,100
We better start.

92
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:07,800
- Okay, let's go.
- Because Mookie has to go.

93
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:10,600
Mommy, Dad...

94
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:16,300
I've already given my pointers
regarding the food.

95
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:20,300
Can I go now?

96
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,233
Please?

97
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:23,267
Okay.

98
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,300
Be safe.

99
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,500
I will.

100
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:26,567
Be safe, okay?

101
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:27,833
Yes.

102
00:06:27,967 --> 00:06:29,700
And can you please call the
coordinator on your way out?

103
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:30,533
Sure.

104
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:33,033
- Thank you.
- Enjoy!

105
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:34,467
Update us.

106
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,567
Miss, they're already there.

107
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,300
Okay, thank you.

108
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,133
Hi.

109
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:49,700
Good evening,
Miss Jade and Mr. Danilo.

110
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,900
We'll be serving
your food in a while.

111
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:53,167
- Okay.
- Enjoy.

112
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,300
- Thank you.
- Okay, thank you.

113
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,700
I'm so ready.

114
00:07:25,033 --> 00:07:26,567
What?

115
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,000
You're spacing out again.

116
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:34,500
I saw how you backed down.

117
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:38,467
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

118
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,567
<i> You, creepy stalker.</i>

119
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,267
I didn't show up to you

120
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,533
because you told me
to stay out of it.

121
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,633
I thought you could
do it on your own.

122
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:55,567
But no, Emma.

123
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,767
You let Jade defeat you.

124
00:07:57,900 --> 00:08:01,100
If this is boxing,
you're already knocked out.

125
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:03,467
Go ahead and insult me.

126
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:06,500
I won't get defeated
if it's only Jade.

127
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:08,633
But I'm thinking about Mookie.

128
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,467
I don't want her to think
I'm a bad person.

129
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,200
I'm a bad mother.

130
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,500
Is there something wrong
with what I said?

131
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:17,367
It's true.

132
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,567
You're no match to Jade.

133
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:24,200
And you let her mess with you.

134
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:25,533
You're dumb.

135
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:27,167
You're so dumb!

136
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:32,267
Do you know why Jade fooled me?

137
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,500
Because she used Mookie.

138
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:38,433
I can't think straight
when Mookie is involved.

139
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:40,900
But she can't mess
with me anymore.

140
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:41,733
There!

141
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:43,533
That's what I'm looking for.

142
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:46,167
Seeing you angry
and wanting to fight.

143
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:49,133
That's the face of someone
who wants revenge.

144
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,600
If Jade wants to play dirty,
then mess with her, too.

145
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,133
How?

146
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,400
Use me.

147
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:26,400
Logan, is this our table?

148
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:27,133
Emma?

149
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,733
- Emma.
- Logan?

150
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,500
Oh, hi!

151
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:34,733
You're here too.

152
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,167
Seriously?

153
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:40,833
Of all the restaurants...

154
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:43,533
and, of all the tables...

155
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,700
you're going to sit there?

156
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:48,367
Yes, this is our reserved table.

157
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:52,533
Let's go, Love.

158
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:53,533
Please?

159
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,067
Thank you.

160
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:08,633
Wine, Sir?

161
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:10,067
Yes, please.

162
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,000
Sir.

163
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:24,233
Go ahead, please.

164
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,233
Thank you.

165
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:42,700
Let me, please.

166
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:44,933
Thank you.

167
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:50,367
How did you manage to
get a reservation here?

168
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:54,333
The manager here is my friend.

169
00:10:54,467 --> 00:10:56,533
He owes me.

170
00:10:56,667 --> 00:11:00,600
When I learned about
Mookie's fake message to you,

171
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:03,033
I called him immediately.

172
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:04,400
So you knew.

173
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:07,000
Why didn't you tell me?

174
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,400
I thought you would fight.

175
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:12,400
I thought you would
attack and fight them.

176
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,933
But you couldn't do anything.

177
00:11:14,067 --> 00:11:15,567
So all of this...

178
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,367
plan B.

179
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,500
Thanks to me.

180
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,333
You should've told me.

181
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:22,667
So, I wouldn't look like a fool.

182
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,533
Don't get mad.

183
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:25,500
We're already here.

184
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:27,267
Let's just enjoy it.

185
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,267
Okay?

186
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:31,867
And don't tell anyone.

187
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,600
I farted.

188
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,500
You really are crazy.

189
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,533
Love, which one do you want
to try first?

190
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,300
The fish?

191
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:42,767
Yes, that one.

192
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:44,233
I like fish.

193
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:48,867
You want some pasta?

194
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,267
Yeah, a little bit.

195
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:55,033
Try this...

196
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:00,300
You know what, Logan?

197
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:02,667
This is the first time
someone cared for me like this.

198
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,700
This is the first time someone
peeled a shrimp for me.

199
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,467
Because I used to be the one
who always took care of them.

200
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,000
Hey.

201
00:12:12,133 --> 00:12:14,500
Don't mention the
name of your ex.

202
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:18,367
Let's just enjoy this night.

203
00:12:19,933 --> 00:12:21,733
They're in an awkward silence.

204
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:24,400
And she looks so annoyed.

205
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:25,333
- Really?
- Yes.

206
00:12:31,533 --> 00:12:33,000
You're enjoying it.

207
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:37,300
Don't tell me you still
have feelings for your ex?

208
00:12:37,433 --> 00:12:38,500
I have...

209
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:42,867
Anger, wrath, deep disgust,
and hatred.

210
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,533
Logan, I'll use the
restroom first.

211
00:12:57,667 --> 00:12:58,700
Okay.

212
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:00,767
I'll start eating, okay?

213
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:01,867
Okay.

214
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:07,733
Love, excuse me.

215
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,367
I'll just go to the restroom.

216
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,367
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

217
00:13:19,067 --> 00:13:20,133
Waiter!

218
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:21,767
More wine, please.

219
00:13:41,533 --> 00:13:45,133
So you're no longer ashamed
to flaunt your lover.

220
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:50,200
You really have a dirty mind.

221
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:52,933
You're so good at accusing.

222
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:56,733
If someone can invent
a mind cleaner,

223
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,500
I'll give you one.

224
00:13:58,633 --> 00:13:59,900
Let Danilo use it too.

225
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:01,667
Because he seems to be
starting to act like you.

226
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:10,033
You think you're funny?

227
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,233
No.

228
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:13,733
I'm not trying to be funny
because I'm not a clown.

229
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:16,133
Waiter!

230
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:17,333
More wine, please.

231
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:22,767
Sir, wine?

232
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:26,033
Yes, please. Thank you.

233
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:27,267
- Is this okay?
- More.

234
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,067
Okay, thank you.

235
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,667
Me too.

236
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,400
Please fill it up.

237
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,533
More. That's good.

238
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:58,200
Why do you hate me so much?

239
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,333
I seem to smell something.

240
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,433
The scent of jealousy?

241
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:14,100
What?

242
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,267
Me?

243
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,500
Jealous?

244
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:22,200
Why?

245
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:25,667
Because my husband,
who you want so badly,

246
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,733
keeps looking at me and Logan.

247
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:30,300
Affected?

248
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:36,267
Are you high or something?

249
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:40,667
Danilo is affected
by you and Logan?

250
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,533
Come on, Jade.

251
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:43,033
Didn't you see that?

252
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:43,867
He keeps drinking.

253
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,467
He's getting drunk.

254
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:48,600
He doesn't seem aware
that you're with him.

255
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:50,933
Because he's focused on us.

256
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:24,033
You know what, Emma?

257
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:25,767
You just changed how you dress,

258
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,167
and now you're acting like
you're all that.

259
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:32,733
Danilo isn't affected
by you and Logan.

260
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,500
He doesn't care
about you anymore

261
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:39,533
because we're already
getting married.

262
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:41,400
Just because
you're getting married

263
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,333
doesn't mean he loves you.

264
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:45,067
Why?

265
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,867
Has he already told you
he loves you?

266
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,967
Yes, you succeeded.

267
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:53,033
You made Danilo
and Mookie hate me.

268
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,167
But I won't back down.

269
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,633
I will prove that
you drove me crazy.

270
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:03,967
That you conspired with
someone in Havenwood.

271
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,633
I'm just starting.

272
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:10,267
Wow.

273
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,800
You're so brave now.

274
00:17:12,933 --> 00:17:14,067
You're so feisty now.

275
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:16,733
Why?

276
00:17:16,867 --> 00:17:18,133
Is it because of Logan?

277
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:23,733
I haven't let him interfere yet.

278
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:25,767
So brace yourself.

279
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:29,233
Because I will now ask him
for help

280
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:31,933
to beat you
and get my daughter back!

281
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:01,200
- Emma.
- Dan.

282
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:03,633
What does that guy
have that I don't?

283
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,667
What?

284
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,500
Love?

285
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:15,300
Dan!

286
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:19,300
What's your problem?

287
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:21,033
You!

288
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,400
You're my problem.

289
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:25,200
Because you weren't
satisfied with me.

290
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:25,967
Stop!

291
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,433
And you looked
for another man.

292
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:28,800
Oh, please! You're drunk.

293
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,667
Emma, what does he
have that I don't?

294
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,500
I want to know.

295
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:35,433
What is it?

296
00:18:35,567 --> 00:18:36,167
Is it this?

297
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:36,967
Hey!

298
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,167
Stop!

299
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:39,333
- Dan! Let me go!
- Is this what you want?

300
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:40,667
Let me go!

301
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,533
- Stop!
- Is he better than me?

302
00:18:42,667 --> 00:18:43,667
Let me go!

303
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:44,633
Dan, what are you doing?

304
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:47,467
- Hey!
- You really are a flirt!

305
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,300
This is all your fault!

306
00:18:49,433 --> 00:18:52,133
They're in a mess
because of you!

307
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:53,600
It's your fault!

308
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:55,267
Because you drove me crazy.

309
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:57,033
But I won't let you win.

310
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:59,233
I will never let you win,
either.

311
00:18:59,367 --> 00:19:01,600
Especially now that
I've gotten your family.

312
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,633
They're mine now, Emma.

313
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,800
They are now mine!

314
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:06,700
Mine!

315
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:07,667
Mine!

316
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:08,900
Mine!

317
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,133
Did I hear it right?

318
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:15,633
Mine?

319
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:19,700
Or maybe the question should be,
is that really you, Jade?

320
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,000
Why?

321
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:25,800
Because you're used to Olive
being the only one

322
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:28,433
who can have an
outburst like this?

323
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,467
I thought my sister was
only paranoid

324
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:31,867
because of her mental state.

325
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,500
That's why she was always angry.

326
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:34,800
But now I understand.

327
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:36,100
Turns out you pushed her
too far.

328
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:39,833
Because you tried to steal
the people she loves!

329
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,200
I knew it.

330
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:45,900
I didn't trust you from the
moment I first saw your face.

331
00:19:46,033 --> 00:19:47,433
Let's go! That's enough!

332
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:49,200
Come on. Let's leave those crazy
people.

333
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:51,967
- Wait. Stop!
- Jade, let's go.

334
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:52,967
What happened to you?

335
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,533
Let's go.

336
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:57,100
I thought you only brought
home a wad of money.

337
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:59,333
But you also came
with a thick face.

338
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:00,400
Why?

339
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:02,000
Is it wrong for me to take
back my daughter,

340
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:04,233
who you keep stealing from me?

341
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:07,400
I know that you
don't love Mookie.

342
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:09,800
You only want
to ruin our family.

343
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:13,267
I don't have to ruin you
in front of your family.

344
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:17,733
Because you ruined yourself!

345
00:20:17,867 --> 00:20:19,267
Don't worry.

346
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,600
Because I'll make you feel
what you made me go through.

347
00:20:22,733 --> 00:20:24,467
What do you call that?

348
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,467
Karma.

349
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:27,767
I don't believe in karma.

350
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,333
Oh, yeah.

351
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:30,833
I forgot.

352
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:33,000
You're worshipping the demon.

353
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:35,567
That's why you don't care,
even if you hurt someone.

354
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:38,333
But I won't let you succeed.

355
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:43,667
And I'll make sure that
Mookie will be mine.

356
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:46,267
Logan, let's go.

357
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:21,800
You saw Jade, right?

358
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:24,467
She seemed to change.

359
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:27,033
We've been together in
Japan for years,

360
00:21:27,167 --> 00:21:30,133
but that was the first time
I saw her have an outburst

361
00:21:30,267 --> 00:21:31,767
like that.

362
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,267
She seemed to be
possessed by someone.

363
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,467
I thought she was
different from Olive.

364
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:43,100
I thought I could learn
to love her as my sister.

365
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:46,633
But she revealed her
bad side right away.

366
00:21:46,767 --> 00:21:49,233
My first impression
of her was right.

367
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:51,567
She and Olive are the same.

368
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:54,533
They both want to ruin my life.

369
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:09,033
What were you thinking
when you talked to Emma?

370
00:22:09,167 --> 00:22:11,967
That woman will become
more delusional.

371
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,800
I only wanted to ask her
something.

372
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:15,600
Love...

373
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,100
look at me.

374
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:22,333
Do you still love Emma?

375
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:26,433
Do you still have
feelings for her?

376
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,000
No.

377
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:32,867
I don't have feelings
for Emma anymore.

378
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:36,833
I don't love her anymore.

379
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:45,700
I don't believe him.

380
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:48,233
And I know that Danilo
can't admit it to himself

381
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,000
because he's consumed
with anger.

382
00:22:50,133 --> 00:22:54,100
But deep inside, he still
has feelings for Emma.

383
00:22:54,233 --> 00:22:55,900
<i>What if you go
on a vacation?</i>

384
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,600
<i>So you can have Mookie
all to yourself</i>

385
00:22:57,733 --> 00:22:58,900
<i> and, of course, Danilo.</i>

386
00:22:59,033 --> 00:23:02,300
<i>Enough for him to realize
that it's you he loves.</i>

387
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:03,500
Staycation?

388
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:05,100
<i> Staycation romance.</i>

389
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:08,167
Did I hear the word staycation?

390
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:10,200
Astrid, I have to go.

391
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,067
Bye.

392
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:14,833
Yes, you heard it right.

393
00:23:14,967 --> 00:23:16,133
Come sit with me.

394
00:23:19,167 --> 00:23:26,033
You, me, and your dad
are going on a staycation.

395
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:28,500
So, wait.

396
00:23:28,633 --> 00:23:32,833
This will be my
first family outing.

397
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:37,067
Thank you, Mommy Jade!

398
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,233
I'm also excited, baby girl.

399
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:40,367
You know what?

400
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,233
You can invite your friends.

401
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:43,633
So you'll have company

402
00:23:43,767 --> 00:23:46,400
while your dad and I
are busy with other things.

403
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:47,400
Sure.

404
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:50,800
Before that,
let's take a picture

405
00:23:50,933 --> 00:23:52,033
to document this moment.

406
00:23:52,167 --> 00:23:53,233
Sure, sure.

407
00:23:57,767 --> 00:23:58,800
One more.

408
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:02,367
Love it!

409
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:03,900
Thank you, Mommy Jade!

410
00:24:04,033 --> 00:24:05,533
I'll just make a call.

411
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:07,067
I'll call my friends.

412
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:07,800
Go ahead.

413
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:09,433
Invite as many as you want.

414
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:10,700
I will!

415
00:24:25,867 --> 00:24:31,000
Life is so much better
without Emma!

416
00:24:36,133 --> 00:24:38,067
Mookie, this is for you.

417
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,633
Thank you, Mommy.

418
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:43,700
Sorry. I got it first.

419
00:24:43,833 --> 00:24:46,200
And even the man
you're going to marry.

420
00:24:46,333 --> 00:24:47,467
Did you see Jade's face earlier?

421
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:50,067
She was so annoyed.

422
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,700
And your ex looked so jealous.

423
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:56,100
Maybe he regrets letting you go.

424
00:24:56,233 --> 00:24:57,867
I will cancel our reservation.

425
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,167
Let's move to another resort.

426
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:00,067
We're not leaving.

427
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,000
What?

428
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:04,067
They'll think we're losers
if we go.

429
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:05,033
Emma.

430
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:07,700
I heard at the reception

431
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:10,033
that Jade is having a poolside
date prepared

432
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,367
for her and Danilo.

433
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:12,300
Maybe that's it.

434
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,133
The gazebo at the center
seems beautiful.

435
00:25:15,933 --> 00:25:17,767
I know what you're thinking.

436
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,167
This will be fun.
